&lt;p&gt;The CWPT Immunisation Service provides school based immunisations in Primary and Secondary schools across Coventry, Warwickshire, Herefordshire, Worcestershire and Solihull.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join us, you must be a first level Registered Nurse with at least I year post registration nursing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally you will have experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with children&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in the community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Immunisation experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must like working with children and young people and have a compassionate manner when dealing with large groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have very good organisational skills and be calm under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have or be prepared to undertake the fundamentals of immunisation training (approx. 10hrs on line) and undertake competencies that accompany this. Further training will also be required in relation to working under a PGD, Paediatric Basic Life Support, There may be occasional evening and weekend work&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
